content.content:
{
  "id": "RULE-1",
  "statement": "First organizing principle: 'Design is the code.' The proof carries structural weight that absorbs the agent's implementation drive at design altitude."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-2",
  "statement": "Second organizing principle: 'The purpose is to create Shared Understanding.' Every mechanism in the design system serves designer-intent capture."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-3",
  "statement": "Third organizing principle: PM-as-decider. Agent generates content (research, framing, drafts, structural placement); designer generates decisions (ratifications, choices, redirects, locks). Agent-generated decisions and PM-supplied technical content are both failure modes."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-4",
  "statement": "Information packet is the fixed-shape per-round content unit the designer reads. Six components: insight + intro + facts (3-5 single-sentence bullets) + agent commentary + pessimist commentary + decision. Designer-locked from cluster-D foundation."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-5",
  "statement": "Single-topic discipline: each round addresses exactly one topic. Multi-topic rounds prohibited; surplus topics queue for subsequent rounds in priority order."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-6",
  "statement": "Closed element set: NC, Evidence, Rule, Permission, Risk, Concern, Resolve Condition, Friction, Phantom, Definition. Extension only by charter-level decision."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-7",
  "statement": "Two-yes closure gate (cluster-B.2 inheritance, D.1 NC-11): closure requires designer consent twice in the same round — first 'yes' on present_closing_argument, second 'yes' on confirm_closure_go. Any mutation between the two clears both flags and forces re-presentation."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-8",
  "statement": "Designer-consent gate on every advancement: every state-mutating proof operation requires a designer-source-or-confirmed consent token with optional rationale. Inherited from D.1 NC-8."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-9",
  "statement": "Agent-rule-submission discipline: only the designer creates Rules. The agent may surface a candidate Rule in commentary for designer ratification but does not auto-add Rules."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-10",
  "statement": "D.1 NC-1 inheritance: open_proof requires problem_statement plus initial seed material (Concerns, Evidence, Rules) at the boundary; restructuring action labels are required on every element."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-11",
  "statement": "D.1 NC-12 inheritance: post-confirm_closure_go state is immutable; explicit reopen_proof is required to amend."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-12",
  "statement": "Voice and Style decision (sprint-d-2 round 2): session Voice and Style are designer-selectable at session start, mid-session mutable; defaults Voice=PM, Style=normal."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-13",
  "statement": "Closing-argument render and design-brief render both use a predetermined briefing voice with normal verbosity. Voice and Style for these two artifacts are not designer-selectable; skill-author-fixed."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-14",
  "statement": "Proof layer contracts are binding."
}
{
  "id": "RULE-15",
  "statement": "Proof layer contracts may not be redesigned."
}

